    "description": "<strong>The Lords of The Earth Flame</strong> is a novel game created in the best traditions of interactive fiction and text-based role-playing. Non-linear structure, rich text core, and the “analog” feel of times past are certain to provide unforgettable gaming experience for hours on end.<br><br>This attempt to revisit the unduly forgotten genre is a curious challenge and possibly the first step toward a full-scale rebirth of non-linear text-based quests. In the developers' enthusiastic view, modern graphics technology and friendly interface may help interactive fiction spring to a new life and find a well-deserved niche of its own on the modern gaming market.<br><br><strong>Plot</strong><br><br>The game's events take place in a fantasy universe closely resembling the Late Middle Ages. Take up the role of a guide to a trade caravan that—by a twist of fate—finds itself in a mountain cave. Your efforts to get out lead you to mysterious ruins, entering which may result in losing more than just your life…<br><br><strong>Game features:</strong><br><br>- atmospheric parchment-scroll interface;<br>- intricate non-linear plot;<br>- mood-setting soundtrack;<br>- replay value;<br>- more than 5 different endings.",
